  <data name="FullDescription" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>A data store flagged as storing credentials (StoresCredentials = Yes) should restrict who can reach it. When its access control is None, Public, or unset, any party that can reach the store can read or tamper with the secrets it holds, leading to information disclosure and elevation of privilege.

This rule is violated for any storage element whose StoresCredentials property is Yes and whose AccessControl property is not RBAC or ACL.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="HelpText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Apply role-based access control (RBAC) or an access control list (ACL) to the store, grant only the identities that need the secrets, and set the store's AccessControl property accordingly.

If the element does not actually hold credentials, correct the StoresCredentials property so the diagram reflects reality.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="MessageText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Data store [{0}] holds credentials but has no meaningful access control, allowing unauthorized parties to read or tamper with the secrets.</value>
